						<div class="postbody">What Sik is referring to is an NMI handler like that used in Concentration Room, Lawn Mower, Thwaite, and Zap Ruder:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">nmi:<br />&nbsp; inc nmis<br />&nbsp; rti</div><br />In before tokumaru points out that doing VRAM updates, the music engine, and the status bar split <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NMI_thread" class="postlink">in the NMI handler</a> makes sure that your music doesn't slow down and your sprite 0 split doesn't have a seizure even if the game slows down.</div>

